<!DOCTYPE html>
<html âš¡>
    <head>
        <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-head.ejs %>
        <link rel="canonical" href="/Quick_Installation/Live_Video/Avast">
    </head>

    <body class="home">

      <amp-sidebar id='sidebar' side='right' layout='nodisplay'>
          <% include ../_partials/amp/_ampLandingSidebar.ejs %>
      </amp-sidebar>

      <header class="header fixed">
        <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-header.ejs %>
      </header>

      <div class="wrap">
          <div class="container main">

              <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-qi.ejs %>

                <section class="blade wrapper content">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="twelve columns">
                                <h1>Avast Internet Security</h1>
                                <h2>Set an Exception for your IP Camera</h2>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    In some cases it can be that the virus scanner "Avast" is blocking the video stream of the camera. Actually it blocks the ActiveX and Quicktime Plugin from receiving the cameras video stream. In this case you will need to set an exception in Avast so it does not block the camera anymore.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 1</strong>: Please open the program Avast by clicking the Avast symbol on the right side of the windows task bar. Another way is to open the start menue and to choose the program directly. Once opened please click Settings on the upper right side.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                          <amp-img
                              on="tap:lightbox1"
                              role="button"
                              tabindex="0"
                              src="/images/Avast_Internet_Security_01_EN.jpg" width="650" height="461" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                          </amp-img>
                          <amp-image-lightbox id="lightbox1" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox>
                            <div>
                                <p>
                                    Open the program configuration.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 2</strong>: In the window Basic settings please select the setting Troubleshoot on the left side.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <amp-img
                                  on="tap:lightbox2"
                                  role="button"
                                  tabindex="0"
                                  src="/images/Avast_Internet_Security_02_EN.jpg" width="650" height="603" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                              </amp-img>
                              <amp-image-lightbox id="lightbox2" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 3</strong>: In the Troubleshooting menu please go to the section Web and select the field Ignored addresses.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <amp-img
                                  on="tap:lightbox3"
                                  role="button"
                                  tabindex="0"
                                  src="/images/Avast_Internet_Security_03_EN.jpg" width="650" height="603" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                              </amp-img>
                              <amp-image-lightbox id="lightbox3" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 4</strong>: Please fill in the IP address of your camera. If you have more then one IP cameras please type in each IP address separated by a comma (,). Now please confirm the settings by clicking OK.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                              <amp-img
                                  on="tap:lightbox4"
                                  role="button"
                                  tabindex="0"
                                  src="/images/Avast_Internet_Security_04_EN.jpg" width="650" height="603" layout="responsive" class="shadow">
                              </amp-img>
                              <amp-image-lightbox id="lightbox4" layout="nodisplay"></amp-image-lightbox>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                        <div class="margin">
                            <div>
                                <p class="justify">
                                    <strong>Step 5</strong>: Finally, please reload the web interface of your IP camera. This can be done by either clicking the refresh button next to the address bar of your web browser or you can close your web browser and re-type the IP address of your camera in the browsers address bar.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /margin -->

                    </div>
                    <!-- /Container -->
                </section>
                <!-- /blade -->
            </div>
            <!-- /Content -->
        </div>
        <!-- /WRAP -->

        <% include ../_partials/content/_bluenav-qi-mobile.ejs %>

        <footer>
            <% include ../_partials/amp/_amp-footer.ejs %>
        </footer>
    </body>
</html>
